reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble and looks nice
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this to give us a place to store our vr headsets that wasn’t the floor. It’s the perfect size for what we needed. The instructions were easy to follow and we put it together pretty fast. The drawer sits in the shelf as opposed to being on tracks which mean you could use it on whichever shelf you like. It comes with the hardware to fasten to the wall which is nice if you have small children and the feet are adjustable to help balance on uneven floors. I feel like it’s a great value for the price and I would definitely order it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and Functional
reviews.reviewText: Bought two of these for a small area needing storage and they are working great! Appear to be sturdy, and are nice looking. One small cabinet did arrive without two holes drilled in a rail, but it was an easy fix with a drill. Instructions are clear, pieces are labeled, and extra parts are supplied. Well worth the money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cheap Chinese RTA shelf - but that's what I paid for
reviews.reviewText: It's a little smaller than I expected, but that's my own fault. My daughter wanted it for her room so I just ordered it without really paying much attention. This is a cheap shelf. The frame is made from low grade, thin, flimsy metal. The shelves are thin with a thin laminate-like surface. Overall though, once assembled, it was sturdier and more functional than I thought it would be. For its small size, it has entirely too many parts to assemble. The metal sections of the sides are around 1 foot sections. I'm sure this is to get it into a small enough box to make delivery costs reasonable. Assembly is pretty straightforward. The directions are actually pretty clear and written in understandable English. I used a battery drill to assemble, but I set the drill clutch on the lowest setting to avoid overtightening. Even that caused the screw heads to pull in a little tight on the thin, flimsy metal. So if you go the power tool route for assembly be extremely careful. I think it would take a long time to assemble using the supplied hex key and screwdriver. Anyway, once assembled it looks nice enough. It's not the type of furniture to survive a move or anything. My teenage daughter wanted it to put some knick-knacks and books on and it serves that purpose well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute, sturdy and easy
reviews.reviewText: I've purchased a few things of this color and materials. I made a glorified closet out of an unused guest room and it's adorable and so very useful. Spreading out your wardrobe and eliminating dresser drawers helps you see things that you forgot you had.The directions are simple and easy to assemble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Part came broken…
reviews.reviewText: I really like this shelving unit, except that one of the ‘A’ pieces, or the actual shelf part, came cracked. I didn’t notice until I was already almost done building it so there’s not much I can do. I wish the company would send me just that one piece so I could replace it. Otherwise the product looks nice and sturdy and was easy to put together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my need
reviews.reviewText: I needed a small bookshelf for my young daughter’s room that fit a small nook behind the door. This is perfect. It’s not too tall, so it won’t fall over and you can put it up against the wall. It it brings you extra tools in case you lose one, and it gives you the tools to connect it up against the wall as well. Easy to build. Just time-consuming, but the directions are very clear. Recommended highly.
